---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Lester Blog" description="About the author of Lester Blog">
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900 sm:p-8">
    <header class="space-y-3">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">About</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 sm:text-4xl">Hi, I’m Lester</h1>
      <p class="text-base text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
        I write about practical web development, static-site architecture, and building maintainable tools.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
      <p>
        This blog shares hands-on notes from real projects: lessons learned, implementation tradeoffs,
        and patterns that scale over time.
      </p>
      <p>
        My focus is shipping simple, durable software using Astro, TypeScript, and modern frontend tooling.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of coding, I enjoy reading technical writing, refining developer workflows, and mentoring engineers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
